Dubai - DWC (DWC), United Arab EmiratesTravel Required:
up to 25%The Panalpina Group is one of the world's leading providers of supply chain solutions, combining its core products of Air Freight, Ocean Freight, and Logistics to deliver globally integrated, tailor-made end-to-end solutions. The Panalpina Group operates a global network with some 500 offices in more than 80 countries, and employs around 15,000 people worldwide.We are looking to hire a Standard & Governance Air Freight Specialist MEAC to cover all Standard & Governance / SAP related tasks for MEAC with the main focus on:i. SAP TM: Product representative for GAP analyzes, Country Simulations and roll outii. Drives electrification of processes through E-Cargo (E-AWB, E-File, E-Booking, C2K)iii. Drives Regional Process Standardization and optimization, increases organizational learningiv. Implements and assures Air Freight Security standards: AMS, Cargo screening, ACAS, etc.ResponsibilitiesProject SAP TM* Product representative GAP analyzes: decision taking if adjustment of standard application is required or if local process requires adjustment, participation GAP analyze in big countries* Training: business input to develop training material, conducts super user training jointly with business transformation in big countries, and prepares process training material* Roll out: supports business transformation in country specific roll outs, searches for effective and efficient process application considering respective country requirementsProject E-Initiate* C2K&PMIP: Assures FWB/FHL quality and penetration and shipment status transparency* E-Freight: establishes regional roll out plan, supports countries in carrier discussion, supports countries in local process set up* E-File: strives towards optimal e-file utilization with the aim to eliminate physical files and reduce local archiving* E-booking: rolls out e-booking for the respective area, assures highest possible customer hit rate General topics* Drives global standardization and guidelines, ensure integration of security aspects in all activities ofAir Freight development and execution* Banned & restricted commodities* Supports RHA in operational excellence matters (definition of standards & guidelines)Qualifications* Profound knowledge of the air freight industry incl. regulatory aspects and Process engineering and improvement methodologies* Good communicator: able to break up complexity and translate it into ops language* Experienced in operational training (all levels)* Preferably higher educational level (economics, logistics)Skills & Competences* Project- and Process management skills* Good ability to integrate and coordinate resources across functions and boundaries, building and using networks, encouraging collaboration across borders, being open to outside input and sharing knowledge and expertise* Independent working attitude* Good ability to organize, including prioritizing, planning, assigning and controlling objectives, drive innovation, manage change and deal with ambiguity, devising effective change management processes* Has a high propensity to travel* Has financial and business awareness* Good knowledge of Microsoft(R) Office Software (Excel(R), Word, PowerPoint(R) and others)* SAP FIN experienceLanguages* Fluent in English (written and spoken)
